<text>Each winner of the 1963 [[Governor General&#x27;s Award]]s for Literary Merit was selected by a panel of judges administered by the Canada Council for the Arts.

==Winners==

===English Language===
*Fiction: Hugh Garner, &quot;Hugh Garner&#x27;s Best Stories&quot;.
*Non fiction: J.M.S. Careless, &quot;Brown of the Globe&quot;.

===French Language===
*Poetry or Drama: Gatien Lapointe, &quot;Ode au Saint-Laurent&quot;.
*Non-Fiction: Gustave Lanctot, &quot;Histoire du Canada&quot;.

